As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 900 people, 408 households, and 250 families residing in the city. The population density was {{convert|2,753.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 514 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,572.3|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the city was 73.33% [[Race (U.S. Census)|White]], 24.89% [[Race (U.S. Census)|Black]] or [[Race (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.33% [[Race (U.S. Census)|Native American]], and 1.44% from two or more races. [[Race (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.33% of the population.

